  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD model employs a steady-state, single-phase incompressible RANS formulation with a power-law hemolysis damage accumulation sub-model. Viscoelastic blood rheology arising from red blood cell aggregation and deformation — a phenomenon known to influence shear-stress distributions in low-shear regions of the pump volute — is excluded from the constitutive model; the blood is treated as a Newtonian fluid with constant viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s. The sensitivity of hemolysis index predictions to this rheological simplification was studied informally by the modelling team during development but is not linked to any documented sensitivity analysis or fidelity trade study.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "conformsToProfile_cou": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileComplete",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
