    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with ASME V&V 40 Table 3 allowances at this risk level. Validation against FDA benchmark PIV data and in-vitro NIH measurements demonstrates model predictive capability within the ±15% acceptance criterion. The Newtonian blood rheology assumption introduces acknowledged model fidelity simplification; the modelling team noted this was studied informally and considered acceptable given the predominantly high-shear operating regime of the CPB pump. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the COU decision at Medium assurance level.",
